  "text": "Bovine endothelial GM7373 cells (Human Genetic Mutual Cell Repository, Camden, NJ) were seeded at 70 000 cells per cm 2 in 24-well plates. After overnight incubation in Eagle's minimal essential medium containing 10% FCS, cells were incubated in medium containing 0.4% FCS and 10 ng/mL FGF2. After 8 hours, increasing concentrations of GAGs were added to cell cultures without changing the medium. Sixteen hours thereafter, cells were trypsinized and counted. [CITATION_1] ",
